p: The essential oil extracted from the leaves of C. anisata was characterized by high levels of phenylpropanoids (84.0%), which were mainly represented by ( E)-anethole (64.6%), with minor contributions by ( E)-methyl isoeugenol (16.1%) and methyl chavicol (2.0%). Terpenoids constituted a minor part of this oil, being represented mostly by p-cymene (2.9%), Î³-terpinene (2.4%), myrcene (2.0%), and germacrene D (2.2%).
